Package com.payd.shooti.utils

Class Container<E>

java.lang.Object
com.payd.shooti.utils.Container<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The generic type to be collected & iterated over
All Implemented Interfaces:
IDispose, IRender, IUpdate, Iterable<E>
Direct Known Subclasses:
EntityManager, ParticleManager
public class Container<E> extends Object implements IRender, IUpdate, IDispose, Iterable<E>

A collection of generic type Container enforcing a queue pattern where elements are only added at the start of the frame, allowing for iteration over the collection without ConcurrentModificationExceptions.


If Container implements IUpdate and/or IRender then the Container will call the IUpdate.update(float) and/or IRender.render(SpriteBatch) methods on each element when the update(float) and/or render(SpriteBatch) methods are called. If Container implements IDispose then the dispose() method will call the IDispose.dispose() method on each element.


Container is a wrapper for LinkedList and HashSet and uses Deque for efficient queueing since v3.0.

Since:
3.1 - Added Iterable interface to allow enhanced-for loop iteration
